The unhype browser extension neutralizes or 'unhypes' clickbait-style headers on web pages. It allows users to configure which elements on a page are processed using CSS selectors and connects to an LLM to rewrite the selected text in a more neutral tone. The extension supports multiple LLM providers, including Ollama, OpenRouter, and Mistral AI.
